(3) The office of a member shall become vacant— (a) upon his death; (b) if he is absent without reasonable excuse from three consecutive meetings of the Governing Board of which he has had notice; (c) on ceasing to be a representative of the organisation which nominated him; (d) if he is an undischarged bankrupt; or (e) if he contravenes section seventeen.
